caption: Food was decent but I will never ever come again. As we paid our tab, the hostess had the nerve to ask if we were or weren’t leaving a tip. I became an unexpected fan of this restaurant. the service is wonderful and the dim sum is excellent. Don't be squeamish try them for yourself lol. and even if that's not your cup of tea (which is also served but sugar is not a usual so asking for it you will be given the sparse amount that pretty much is your recommended daily allowance lol) but you will not be disappointed, enjoy!!

I was here for a friend's wedding. I found the service was very good. There was prompt response to requests for more beer, tea, ice water, silverware, and napkins. I'm afraid the food was pretty mediocre. Sometimes at a wedding, the food waits on wedding reception activities. We were served many seafood dishes, which were generally overcooked, or perhaps the dishes were cooked and sat overly long underneath a heat lamp. The food wasn't very tasty or not seasoned at all.  I feel that the restaurant didn't show their best efforts that day.   I don't plan on going back to try them again.

I've frequented Golden Imperial a couple times now for their private party room with karaoke. While the sound system is great, it's completely in Chinese and not always easy to navigate if you can't read in Chinese. We usually just press buttons and try our best and manage to get to some decent songs that we like.  Food wise I haven't been let down by the restaurant. All around pretty good quality, tasty, and fast. Though one or two times they took plates away while there was still food on the plate but it's not the end of the world. Sharing lots of dishes family style is definitely the way to go here. Their cold lobster salad dish is excellent and a must try if you can!

Arrived here for dinner, and the place was empty. This is a huge restaurant, with plenty of hosting potential. I believe it's 2 stories, and probably makes a ton from dim sum alone. Which is why I was so disappointed, because the food sucked. I'm sorry. Who messes up Peking Pork Chop? They offer a lot on their menu that the cooks do not know how to make. Maybe I will return when they hire some top chefs. But I'll be discreet about it. Just like the Michelin Star people.

Great spot for some authentic Chinese food. Has large private rooms upstairs for events.

Great Dim Sum on afternoons, restaurant in the evening and Banquet Hall. Fresh seafood. Clean place. Upstairs has several large private rooms for parties (I would say can accommodate 50+ people). There is usually at least 1 manager or waiter on duty that speaks English so don't worry about not speaking Chinese. The menu has English translation but it's not the best. Don't waste your time with that delivery excuse for Chinese food. This is the real deal. Somewhat on the pricey side though. Also often there are weddings at night so it may be loud/crowded.
Great food

It was amazing we loved everything!! From the salsa and chips to the desert.  My bf and I ordered the whole chicken for 2 which comes with sweet plantains, rice and beans and French fries (which we replaced for yuca fries) and avocado. Absolutely delish! The margaritas are large enough to share for two; so we started with a mango margarita in the signature patron bottle, and ended it off with a coconut margarita which I highly recommend!! The service and ambiance was great. And for checking in we got a free flan that was simply ok. But overall we had a great experience. Two thumbs up!

Excellent Cantonese food.  My family has gone there for many years.  Nice decor and clean. Food is excellent. Oh I said that already. I am sure their English can be better. But you don't go there to learn English, you go there to have good food.
Solid dim sum offering, has parking lot in front. Gets busy, but they handle the volume well.

A most unexpected suprise. Brooklyn's Chinatown is for real.  My frienss and I went for dinner.  Service was as good as you could expect with the language barrior as nobody seemed to speak english.  The decor is a pastel lovers dream.  The food was traditional and outstanding.  My party and I took turns pointing at the menu and everything was deliescious.  They even were able to cook up some soup dumplings for us special as theybare ussualy a lunch time dim sum special. If you like traditional Chinese food, it would be hard to do better in Brooklyn.
